File: The COVID-19 outbreak originated in the Chinese city of Wuhan in November before spreading globally. JOHANNESBURG - At least a 122 countries are supporting calls for an independent investigation into the origins of the coronavirus. A draft resolution set to be voted on at this week's World Health Assembly was first proposed by Australia on Monday. READ: WHO says virus 'natural in origin' China says it is too early for such an investigation. Although the country wasn't mentioned by name in the draft resolution, the investigation is highly likely to look into how China handled the outbreak. The COVID-19 outbreak originated in the Chinese city of Wuhan in November before spreading globally.